meanings.sent1: She outclimbed her friend to reach the mountain top first.
meanings.sent2: The skilled climber outclimbed all the others in the competition.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outclimbed the cat to get to the top of the tree.
meanings.sent4: His determination outclimbed his fear of heights as he scaled the cliff.
meanings.sent5: The spider outclimbed the fly, spinning its web higher and higher.

meanings.definition: To climb higher or faster than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The athlete outclimbed his own record, reaching the peak in record time.
meanings.sent2: The helicopter easily outclimbed the other aircraft in the sky.
meanings.sent3: The monkey outclimbed the zookeeper, swinging from branch to branch.
meanings.sent4: Her ambition outclimbed her doubts as she ascended the corporate ladder.
meanings.sent5: The rocket outclimbed the clouds, disappearing into the vastness of space.
